              }
}
Node "F1"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "As you've already taken the liberty to point out, the reactor is currently being maintained by Mr. Handy robots. Several years ago, their logic cricuits were re-coded to allow for the maintenance of the coolant systems. However, the models that we received were the Mr. Handy Home Helpers, which are obviously not designed for reactor maintenance. Also, they came equipped with the standard Mr. Handy operating system."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Continue]." linkto "Handy3"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "F1-2"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "As you've already pointed out, the reactor is currently being maintained by Mr. Handy robots. Several years ago, their logic cricuits were re-coded to allow for the maintenance of the coolant systems. However, the models that we received were the Mr. Handy Home Helpers with the standard Mr. Handy OS. Obviously, they are poorly suited for reactor maintenance."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Continue]." linkto "Handy3"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "F2"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "There's no need to be alarmed. Our files are simply used to track your performance and to determine whether or not you are eligible for promotion. Everybody has one, even the Board members."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Would you mind if I take a look?" linkto "G1" conditions { CHECK_STAT perception < 6 link_next NONE } notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I'd like to take a look what you've got, if that's ok." linkto "G2" conditions { CHECK_STAT perception > 5 link_next NONE } notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Oh, I see. Lets get back to the matter at hand, shall we?" linkto "F1"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "G1"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Sure. [Reading through the file, you see that he was telling the truth. Most of the stuff in here is pretty mundane: birth record, medical information, the works. All in all, your file is everything that you would expect a corporate file to be.]"
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Give him back the file.] Let's get back to why you need me." linkto "F1"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "G2"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Sure. [You take the file and skim through it. Most of the documents are pretty standard: birth certificate, medical records, and performance reports. However, towards the end you come across what seems to be a psychiatric evaluation. Most of it is complete gibberish to you - whoever wrote this used obscure technical terms that you aren't familiar with. However, you do notice several references to your \"tractable\" and \"uskeptical\" nature. Also, there seems to have been a memo or something attached to this sheet of paper; there is a scrap of paper stapled to the top of the page. Although most of it is missing, you can read the words \"Ideal\" and \"unassuming\".]"
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Give him back the file.] Lets get back to business, shall we?" linkto "F1"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Handy1"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "As I am sure you are aware, there was a falling out between the Technicians and the Board several years ago. When the CEO died the ensuing power struggle nearly led to violence. In fact, bloodshed was only averted because the upper floors were locked down and the Armory put under constant surveillance. A deal was struck between some of the more reasonable Technicians and the Board: the Technicians would remain in the Vault and run it's primary systems in return for a safe haven. However, the Board was leery of giving Technicians access to the reactor. They didn't want to jeopardize their grip on the Vault."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Continue.]" linkto "Handy2"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I didn't want a history lesson, Ken. What do you want?" linkto "Handy4"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Handy2"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "This left the Board in a difficult position. The reactor had been customized for increased power output through the use of high-grade fuel. In order to speed the installation and conserve space, the reactor didn't have complete radiation shielding when it was installed. Up until the incident, the Techs had been using special suits to enter the reactor room and perform maintenance. Unfortunately, all the suits were destroyed by the Board during the revolution, who feared the Techs would use them to sabotage the reactor."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I think I see where this is headed..." linkto "Handy3"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Handy3"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "Since there were no suits left, human maintenance was impossible. The Board turned to the only other resource available: the robots. They seemed like the ideal choice, being immune to radiation and not the least bit inclined towards revolting. Using the manual that came with them the programming technician, Duane, added a new function to their logic circuits. The robots are now responsible for the maintenance of the coolant systems."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Oh god. Don't tell me that..." linkto "Handy4"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Handy3-1"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "As you may or may not know, the reactor room is fatal to living beings. The reactor has been leaking radiation for many years now, and anyone who enters will receive a terminal dose in less than 15 minutes. The Mr. Handies do not suffer from the same shortcomings, which is why we use them."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "So what is wrong with the Mr. Handies?" linkto "Handy4"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Handy4"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "The Mr. Handies were fine until just recently. According to Duane, the reprogramming of their logic circuits resulted in a slow memory leak, which will eventually overload them and cause an irreversible shutdown. At the same time, the leak is impairing their ability to regulate the coolant systems. Every day, the reactor temperature rises a fraction of a degree. At this point, we project 60 days until the reactor reaches critical temperature and there is a meltdown."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "[Continue]." linkto "Handy5"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Handy5"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "We have a solution, however. We discovered that there is a way to undo the damage that the memory leak has caused - reinstall the Mr. Handy OS. Unfortunately, we didn't receive a copy of the software. In fact, the only place we know of that had copies on hand was the local General Atomics International office. That, <PC>, is where you come in."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Let me guess..." linkto "Want1"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Refusal1"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "[He is obviously shocked] Well, I... You mean you don't care about the lives of the people in this Vault? You don't want to save your friends, your family, or anybody else?"
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "I didn't create the problem. You did." linkto "Refusal2"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "It's not that. I just don't feel like I can handle the responsibilty." linkto "Refusal3"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Well... Since you put it that way -" linkto "Team1"  notes ""
              }
}
Node "Refusal2"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
NPCText "True, but nobody could have foreseen this situation. Everything was running normally until just recently."
      options {
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "You are the ones who reprogrammed the Mr. Handies, not me." linkto "Refusal4"  notes ""
          int=4 Reaction=REACTION_NEUTRAL playertext "Do you think you can just manipulate me and get whatever you want? I'm not going to be your pawn." linkto "H1" conditions { CHECK_STAT perception > 5 link_next NONE } notes ""
              }
}
Node "Refusal3"
notes ""
is_wtg = false
{
